"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-25-paris-2024-olympics-super-falcons-not-scared-of-brazil-ajibade\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons captain, Rasheedat Ajibade, has declared the team's readiness for the clash with Brazil.  DAILY POST reports that the nine-time African champions will be up against the Samba Girls in their first game in the women's football event at the 2024 Olympic Games on Thursday (today).  The encounter at the Matmut Atlantique Stadium, Bordeaux will kick-off at 6pm Nigeria time.  Brazil defeated the Super Falcons in their previous two meetings and are the overwhelming favourites to win the upcoming tie.  Ajibade, however, said the Super Falcons are battle ready for the task ahead.  \\\"Playing in professional leagues, we encounter many players from different countries, including Brazil,\\\" Ajibade was quoted by 54footballx.  \\\"I can provide the team with insights on how specific players operate, especially those I have played with or against in Spain and Brazil. We can pool our knowledge to help the team succeed in the Olympics.\\\"  I have got a lot to learn - Reece James on new Chelsea position under Maresca  Transfer: Rudiger takes decision on leaving Real Madrid  'I am upset, sad' - Neymar reacts after being dropped by Ancelotti from Brazil's squad  Real reason I did not include Neymar in Brazil squad - Ancelotti  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"